The paper proposes a novel neural network architecture for human action recognition in videos, which involves dimensionality reduction, Gaussian mixture model, and Fisher vector descriptor extraction. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with video processing, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the refinement of the model in an end-to-end fashion, which suggests that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
